Document: SkeletonModification2DJiggle
Path: godot/classes/class_skeletonmodification2djiggle.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for configuring a SkeletonModification2DJiggle node, including damping, gravity, mass, stiffness, and target node path.

Properties:
- damping (float): The default amount of damping applied to the Jiggle joints, if they are not overridden. Higher values lead to more of the calculated velocity being applied. Default: 0.75.
  Method: set_damping(value: float)
  Method: get_damping()
- gravity (Vector2): The default amount of gravity applied to the Jiggle joints, if they are not overridden. Default: Vector2(0, 6).
  Method: set_gravity(value: Vector2)
  Method: get_gravity()
- jiggle_data_chain_length (int): The amount of Jiggle joints in the Jiggle modification. Default: 0.
  Method: set_jiggle_data_chain_length(value: int)
  Method: get_jiggle_data_chain_length()
- mass (float): The default amount of mass assigned to the Jiggle joints, if they are not overridden. Higher values lead to faster movements and more overshooting. Default: 0.75.
  Method: set_mass(value: float)
  Method: get_mass()
- stiffness (float): The default amount of stiffness assigned to the Jiggle joints, if they are not overridden. Higher values act more like springs, quickly moving into the correct position. Default: 3.0.
  Method: set_stiffness(value: float)
  Method: get_stiffness()
- target_nodepath (NodePath): The NodePath to the node that is the target for the Jiggle modification. This node is what the Jiggle chain will attempt to rotate the bone chain to. Default: NodePath("").
  Method: set_target_node(value: NodePath)
  Method: get_target_node()
- use_gravity (bool): Whether the gravity vector, gravity, should be applied to the Jiggle joints, assuming they are not overriding the default settings. Default: false.
  Method: set_use_gravity(value: bool)
  Method: get_use_gravity()
